definition: restitution/return of something to its original owner/remittance
still/still in progress/still more/yet/even more/in addition/fairly/passably (good)/as early as/even/also/else

sentences.english: At the end of the term, you typically get no cash back.
sentences.chinese: 固定年限到期後，你一般不會得到任何現金返還。

sentences.english: If no domain is registered, the money is refunded in full.
sentences.chinese: 如果客戶沒有註冊任何域名，那麼保證金將全部返還。

sentences.english: If Exposure decreases, the Transferee is obliged to return equivalent Collateral.
sentences.chinese: 當風險敞口降低時，受讓人有責任返還相同的擔保品。

sentences.english: Refund of outstanding tuition fees will be calculated based on the date written notification was received by SRIS .
sentences.chinese: 學費返還金額將從學校收到書面退學通知之日起計算。

sentences.english: The relationship between the right of the claim for unjust enrichment and other request.
sentences.chinese: 不當得利返還請求權與其他請求權的關係。

sentences.english: Upon expiration of the lease, the Leasee shall return the Leased Vehicle and effective certificates on schedule.
sentences.chinese: 租賃期滿，應按時返還租賃車輛及有效證件。

sentences.english: Article 109 A lost-and-found object shall be returned to the right holder.
sentences.chinese: 第一百零九條拾得遺失物，應當返還權利人。

sentences.english: You can pay only half of the invoiced amount for packing if you return the empty boxes.
sentences.chinese: 如果您返還空箱子，您只需支付一半的包裝費用。

sentences.english: The lawful property of the victims shall be returned to them without delay.
sentences.chinese: 對被害人的合法財產，應當及時返還。

sentences.english: Method of redelivery and conditions for early redelivery.
sentences.chinese: 返還方式及提前返還條件。

sentences.english: Method of redelivery and conditions for early redelivery.
sentences.chinese: 返還方式及提前返還條件。

sentences.english: A tax return-to-tax provision comparison should be done with all differences adequately explained.
sentences.chinese: 比較稅返還和稅準備金應有各個方面的適當解釋。

sentences.english: The recipients shall sign or affix their seals to the list of returned distraint.
sentences.chinese: 領取人應當在返還款物清單上簽名或者蓋章。

sentences.english: The regulation requires the banks to assign case-specific personnel in charge of returning the telecom fraud money.
sentences.chinese: 規定要求銀行指定專人負責電信詐騙資金返還工作。

sentences.english: After the liability is verified, Part A shall return the mould cost paid by Party B.
sentences.chinese: 覈實責任後，甲方返還乙方所支付的模具費。

sentences.english: The key of no-tillage is the supply the past crop residue to soil.
sentences.chinese: 實行免耕制，關鍵是有機殘體的返還。

definition: to return (sth borrowed etc)/to send back/to refund/to rebate
to demand payment of money owing
to break a promise/to violate an agreement/to default (on a loan or contract)
to reduce or waive (taxes, punishment, rent, tuition etc)
to repay a debt in full/to redeem/to clear
